tick

public void tick()
This method should be called each time the Coordinator has to make Monsters move. Calling the method represents the passage of a unit of time in AIMTD's internal clock. After tick() completes, each Monster that's active in the Coordinator will have moved according to its position, speed, intelligence level, surrouding Towers, and various other game factors. Please refer to the Monster and Tower classes for definitions of moveSpeed and fireSpeed, respectively, and their relationship to tick().
